---
import { homeownershipData, mobileData } from "../../data/charts";
import BarChart from "../charts/BarChart.astro";
import TreemapChart from "../charts/TreemapChart.astro";
---

<section id="housing" aria-labelledby="housing-heading">
	<div class="two-col housing-layout">
		<div class="col-text">
			<div class="section-label reveal-left">Housing &amp; Rent</div>
			<h2 id="housing-heading" class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.1s">
				Shelter as<br />Speculation
			</h2>
			<p>
				Housing has been transformed from a basic human need into a
				financial asset class. Homeownership rates are collapsing for
				younger cohorts across the Anglosphere while rents consume an
				ever-larger share of wages already suppressed by the dynamics
				shown above. In the UK, homeownership among 25–34 year-olds fell
				from around 59% in the early 2000s to 28% in 2025. London's house
				price to earnings ratio has more than tripled from around 4:1 to
				nearly 13:1 in a generation.
			</p>
			<p>
				This is rentier capitalism in its purest form: passive income
				derived from ownership, not production. Global real estate —
				valued at $380 trillion (2021, Savills) — is the single largest
				asset class on earth, dwarfing equities, government debt, and gold
				combined. Corporate landlords, private equity firms, and
				speculative investors have turned shelter into a tradeable
				commodity. The result is a generation locked out of ownership and
				locked into extractive rents.
			</p>
			<div class="pull-quote reveal">
				<blockquote>
					"The landlord who happens to own a piece of ground on the
					outskirts of a great city… watches the busy figures multiplying
					around him… and all the while sits still and does nothing."
				</blockquote>
				<cite>— Winston Churchill, 1909</cite>
			</div>
			<p class="source">
				Source:
				<a href="https://www.jchs.harvard.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Harvard JCHS</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ONS</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.resolutionfoundation.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resolution Foundation</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.savills.com/research_articles/255800/334844-0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Savills Global Research</a> ·
				<a href="https://england.shelter.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Shelter</a>
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-charts">
			<div class="stat-grid reveal">
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-0">
					<div class="num" data-target="50" data-prefix="" data-suffix="%">0%</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-0">
						Of US renters spend 30%+ of income on rent — Harvard JCHS 2025<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Harvard JCHS 2025" aria-expanded="false" data-source="Harvard JCHS, State of the Nation's Housing, 2025" data-url="https://www.jchs.harvard.edu/state-nations-housing-2025">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-1">
					<div class="num" data-target="13" data-prefix="" data-suffix=":1">0:1</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-1">London house price to earnings ratio — was around 4:1 in 1997</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-2">
					<div class="num" data-target="380" data-prefix="$" data-suffix="T">$0T</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-2">
						Global real estate value — the largest asset class on earth (2021, Savills)<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Savills 2021" aria-expanded="false" data-source="Savills, Around the World in Dollars and Cents, 2021" data-url="https://www.savills.com/impacts/market-trends/the-total-value-of-global-real-estate.html">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-3">
					<div class="num" data-target="1" data-prefix="" data-suffix="M">0M</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-3">Nearly 1 million empty homes in England while over 350,000 are homeless (Action on Empty Homes 2024; Shelter 2024)</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">Homeownership Rate by Age — UK, 1997 vs 2025</figcaption>
				<div role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing UK homeownership rate decline for 25-34 year-olds: around 59% in the early 2000s versus 28% in 2025">
					<BarChart id="homeownership-chart" items={homeownershipData} />
				</div>
			</figure>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.12s">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">Global Asset Classes by Value</figcaption>
				<div id="asset-treemap-desktop-chart" class="desktop-chart" role="img" aria-label="Treemap showing global asset classes by value: Real estate dominates at $380 trillion">
					<TreemapChart />
				</div>
				<div id="asset-treemap-mobile-chart" class="mobile-chart" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing global asset classes by value">
					<BarChart id="treemap-mobile-bars" items={mobileData.treemap} outsideValueThreshold={5} />
				</div>
				<table class="sr-only">
					<caption>Global Asset Classes by Value</caption>
					<thead><tr><th>Asset Class</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>$380T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Equities</td><td>$109T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Government Debt</td><td>$66T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Gold</td><td>$14T</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</figure>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
